not all sidecars:
-------------
Types of containers in a Pod:
  ├── Init Container      ← separate category
  ├── Sidecar Container   ← main category
  │    ├── Adapter        ← type of sidecar
  │    └── Ambassador     ← type of sidecar
  └── Main Container      ← your actual app
------------------

1. Init Container

A container that runs before the main container starts and then stops.

Wait for database       --  Wait until DB is ready before app starts
Download config files   --  Pull configs before app needs them


initContainers:
  - name: wait-for-db
    image: busybox
    command: ['sh', '-c', 'until nc -z mysql 3306; do sleep 2; done']       or  command: ['sleep', '30']
mainContainer:
  - name: my-app
    image: my-app:latest


2. Sidecar Container (Multi Container)

A helper container that runs along with main container inside same pod.

How it Works

Pod
 ├── Main Container (your app)
 └── Sidecar Container (helper)
        ↓
Both run SIMULTANEOUSLY
        ↓
Share same network and storage


use cases

Log collection    --   Sidecar collects and ships logs

Monitoring        --   Sidecar sends metrics to Prometheus


3. Adapter Container

Every app writes logs in different formats!

Python App logs →  2026-04-07 ERROR NullPointerException
Ruby App logs  →  [FATAL] :: 07/Apr/2026 :: DB Connection failed
Go App logs    →  {"level":"error","time":"2026-04-07","msg":"timeout"}
Java App logs  →  07-Apr-2026 [ERROR] Thread-1 OutOfMemoryError

Problem ⚠️

Monitoring tool cannot understand all different formats

Every app log have different format for python, rupy and go have will have different log format helper(sidecar) container converts output of main container log into a standard format(JSON).

A sidecar that transforms or converts output of main container into a standard format.


4. Ambassador Container

A sidecar that acts as a proxy between main container and outside world.

How it Works

Main Container
wants to connect to database
        ↓
Doesnt connect directly
        ↓
Ambassador Container acts as proxy
        ↓
Handles connection, retries, routing
        ↓
Returns response to Main Container


Real World Example Together


Pod starts
    ↓
Init Container → waits for DB to be ready
    ↓
Main Container → runs your application
    ↓
Adapter Sidecar → converts logs to JSON format
    ↓
Ambassador Sidecar → proxies DB connections safely
    ↓
Everything works perfectly! 🚀
